# No em dashes on this site

Do **not** use the em dash character (Unicode U+2014) anywhere in this project’s authored content: HTML user-facing copy, meta descriptions, `style.md`, README, comments in first-party JS/CSS if they set tone for copy, etc.

**Do not** use HTML `&mdash;` in templates either.

**Prefer instead:**

- Comma or period for a light break
- Colon before an explanation or list
- Hyphen (`-`) for compound modifiers (e.g. decision-desk work)
- The word **to** for ranges (e.g. 2025 to Present)

Third-party code under `node_modules` is excluded; do not edit vendored files for this.

When editing pages, if you see an em dash, replace it (do not introduce new ones). See `style.md` in the project root for the full house style.
